              "uuid": "966724ab-2259-4586-ac54-7c58f834148d",
              "name": "AMA #4: Maintain Motivation, Improve REM Sleep, Set Goals, Manage Anxiety & More",
              "datePublished": 1677243600,
              "description": "<p>Welcome to a preview of the fourth Ask Me Anything (AMA) episode, part of the <a href=\"https://hubermanlab.com/premium\">Huberman Lab Premium</a> subscription.</p><p>The Huberman Lab Premium subscription was launched for two main reasons. First, it was launched in order to raise support for the standard Huberman Lab podcast channel — which will continue to come out every Monday at zero-cost. Second, it was launched as a means to raise funds for important scientific research. A significant portion of proceeds from the Huberman Lab Premium subscription will fund human research (not animal models) selected by Dr. Huberman, with a dollar-for-dollar match from the <a href=\"https://www.tiny.foundation/\">Tiny Foundation</a>.</p><p>Subscribe to Huberman Lab Premium at <a href=\"https://hubermanlab.com/premium\">https://hubermanlab.com/premium</a></p><h2>Timestamps</h2><p>(00:00:00) Introduction</p><p>(00:01:27) How to achieve consistent state of motivation? [Martin Zokov]</p><p>In the full AMA episode, we discuss:</p><ul>\n<li>Are there neurological benefits from different types of body work?</li>\n<li>Are goals necessary for the growth mindset and how to set the best short and long-term goals for creativity?</li>\n<li>Is anxiety useful? Can it be controlled?</li>\n</ul><p><br></p><p>Title Card Photo Credit: <a href=\"https://www.blabacphoto.com/\">Mike Blabac</a></p><p><a href=\"https://hubermanlab.com/disclaimer/\">Disclaimer</a></p>",
