              "name": "MISSING: Denise Pflum",
              "datePublished": 1687158000,
              "description": "<p>On a Friday afternoon in 1986, 18-year-old Denise Pflum leaves her home in Connersville, Indiana, to go searching for a purse she had left at a party the night before. When she doesn’t return home, it’s just the beginning of a nightmare that will haunt her parents for over thirty years.</p><ul><li>If you have any information about the disappearance of Denise Pflum, please contact the Fayette County Sheriff’s Department at 765-222-1272.</li></ul><p> </p><p>Did you know you can listen to this episode ad-free? Join the Fan Club! Visit <a href=\"https://crimejunkieapp.com/library/\"><strong>https://crimejunkieapp.com/library/</strong></a> to view the current membership options and policies.</p><p>Source materials for this episode cannot be listed here due to character limitations. For a full list of sources, please visit: <a href=\"https://crimejunkiepodcast.com/missing-denise-pflum/\" target=\"_blank\">https://crimejunkiepodcast.com/missing-denise-pflum/</a></p>\n",
