              "uuid": "46e38125-bc04-4ccb-b867-36d01907d346",
              "name": "Episode 457: H.H. Holmes Part 1",
              "datePublished": 1683529200,
              "description": "<p>When Boston police arrested Dr. Henry Howard Holmes in a West End boarding house on November 17, 1894, they assumed they had apprehended an interstate criminal guilty of defrauding the Fidelity Insurance company of $10,000 and of being a horse thief in Texas. Holmes had been tracked to New England by the Pinkerton Detective Agency, who had suspected him of other crimes in various cities across the country; yet even the most seasoned and creative detective couldn’t have imagined the horrific scope and magnitude of crimes he’d committed.</p><p><br></p><p>Thanks Dave for this magnificent synopsis!</p><p><br></p><p><em>Thanks to Care/of for being a sponsor of this episode. For 50% off your first Care/of order, go to&nbsp;</em><a href=\"http://takecareof.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><em>TakeCareOf.com</em></a><em>&nbsp;and enter code MORBID50.</em></p><p>See Privacy Policy at <a href=\"https://art19.com/privacy\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://art19.com/privacy</a> and California Privacy Notice at <a href=\"https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info</a>.</p>",
